The paper discusses the use of Knowledge Graphs (KGs) in various AI applications such as link prediction, entity relations prediction, node classification, recommendation, and question answering systems. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also talks about the structured representation of real-world information, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The use of KGs in search engines and information retrieval systems suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the challenges of representing changing nodes, attributes, and edges over time, which is a research problem in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of KGs in various AI applications involves machine learning techniques, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
